   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Lombard Asia IV</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Lombard Asia IV L.P. (Lombard Asia IV or the Fund), a Cayman Islands exempted limited partnership, is a private equity fund seeking $400 million in capital commitments to build a portfolio of equity and equity-linked investments in middle market, growth-oriented companies formed and operated in Southeast Asia.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Fund would help its portfolio companies create jobs, potentially covering the rural areas and increasing female employment.  The Fund would help private sector development through supporting growth and operational improvement of its portfolio companies.  The Project would support private equity investments in the Fund&apos;&apos;s target markets, helping develop the financial markets in its target countries.</narrative>
  </description>
